<br>
Doesn't the earth pet cast root? Meh.  I haven't toyed with a magician in a looooooong time.  All in all, I'm a bit distressed.  Ice Comet is the real thing that is bothering me.  Rend, pillar of frost, and atol's to a lesser extent.  I understand the need for an upgrade, with their flimsy HP and all, but I think it's just a wee bit overboard, unless the pets get more aggro from casting said spells so they splat sooner.<br>
<br>
I think they should drop it a bit.  Maybe giving it Conflag instead of Ice Comet and maybe Enticement of Flame or Force Strike to replace Rend.  Atol's... ah... giving the pet a single target snare would probably be better.  Atol's makes sense.  The magician and his little boomer buddy are going to be generating a lot of aggro and I wouldn't be surprised if they caught the attention of more than one mob.  Atol's is a bit of a defined wizard spell - AE snare anyways is.<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost... well, I can't say I like it on a pet, but I'm not sure why you'd want it on a pet.  You'd need another serious revamp of pet AI or superb pet controlling abilities not to get yourself, and your group, killed.<br>
<br>
Someone posted they also use Lures?  That's crossing the line.  Even if the ratio isn't fantastic and they are no longer as needed as much, take the lures away.  Pets should not have a lures - a wizard defining nuke.<br>
<br>
Other than that, the changes look pretty good.<br>
<br>
